               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-1282" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1282" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1282" type="surname" value="CARLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1282" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS CARLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a smith and engineer, and live at Lambeth. On Thursday, the 27th of May, I had some old metal cocks and other things—I did not miss them till the policeman came about five o'clock on Sun<lb></lb>day afternoon—it was a lot of old brass—it was useful, but was put away</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183706120165"></xptr>
               <p>as old, but some of it was new—I had seen it in the shop about the middle of the day on the 27th—the prisoner worked for me—the brass was pro<lb></lb>duced to me by the policeman on Sunday—it is my property.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-1283" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1283" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1283" type="surname" value="COOKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1283" type="given" value="EDWARD CHARLES"></interp>EDWARD CHARLES COOKE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was on duty at Lambeth on the 28th of May at five o'clock in the morning, and saw the prisoner with a bag containing these articles—I stopped him and asked what he had there—he would not satisfy me—I turned it out, and found it was metal—I asked where he was going with it—he said, "Down there"—I asked where he got it—he said, he brought it from Lambeth.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to.</hi>)</p>
